  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is an open label study of subjects who have failed Protocol PGN-1300. Adult subjects
      (greater than 18 years old) who present with a mildly infected diabetic foot ulcer (IDSA
      criteria) having full thickness (i.e., through the dermis but not involving joint capsule,
      tendon, and bone) and have failed PGN-1300. Subjects must also provide informed consent and
      meet all other entry criteria to be enrolled and receive PluroGel PN.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
